prompt: INVOICE EXTRACTION INSTRUCTIONS:    1. The overall invoice total should NEVER be assigned as a price to any individual line item. 2. Column headers (like \\\"PART IDENTIFICATION\\\", \\\"Line No\\\", \\\"QTY SHIP\\\", \\\"EXT AMT\\\") are not line item descriptions - don't confuse them with actual product descriptions. 3. Line items without explicit unit prices should have zero values for price fields, not the invoice total. 4. On the final page of multi-page invoices, distinguish between:\n   - The invoice TOTAL (belongs in header.total)\n   - Individual line items (need their own specific prices, if shown only) 5. Line items showing only reference information without explicit pricing should have zero price values. 6. Do not use \\\"Part Identification\\\" as a description - this is a column header, not the actual description. 7. For each line item, verify that the price comes from the appropriate unit price or amount column for that specific item only. 8. Differentiate between actual line items and summary information - summary totals belong in the header, not as line items. 9. Extract the Quantity and Line No for each line item:  - If a line item spans multiple pages, the quantity may appear on an earlier page, and the line number on a later one — these must be correlated and combined.  - Some items may not have a line number — in such cases, leave the line number field blank or null.  - The line number is often found in the 4th line of the item description block — parse accordingly to extract it. 10. Pay special attention to items at page breaks - these may appear to be continued items but are often distinct line items with their own quantities and values. 11. Each distinct part number and quantity combination represents a separate line item. Do not merge similar items. special_instructions: 1. Quantities: Always whole numbers followed by EA (e.g., 875.000 EA); extract as integers from the 'QTY SHIP' column. 2. Weight: The 'WT' column indicates weight, not quantity — do not confuse the two. 3. Unit Price: Includes an 'M' suffix, meaning price per thousand units — adjust calculations accordingly. 4. Extended Amount: Extract from the 'EXT AMT' column; sum all line items to validate the subtotal/total. 5. Line Items: - Extract item code from PART IDENTIFICATION (e.g., NA002472) - apture full description as shown - Extract tool numbers (e.g., NA035214 TWO SHOT) - Extract line numbers (e.g., Line No: 1.000) - Extract weight, unit price, and extended amount individually 6. Header Info: - Supplier name: Must be exactly 'Stanley Engineered Fastening LLC' - Invoice number, invoice date, and page info: capture precisely - 'Sales Order No.' is the PO number (e.g., 13665335) - Data Separation: Keep tool numbers, line numbers, and customer references as distinct fields.

special_instructions: 1. Quantities: Always whole numbers followed by EA (e.g., 875.000 EA); extract as integers from the 'QTY SHIP' column. 2. Weight: The 'WT' column indicates weight, not quantity — do not confuse the two. 3. Unit Price: Includes an 'M' suffix, meaning price per thousand units — adjust calculations accordingly. 4. Extended Amount: Extract from the 'EXT AMT' column; sum all line items to validate the subtotal/total. 5. Line Items: - Extract item code from PART IDENTIFICATION (e.g., NA002472) - apture full description as shown - Extract tool numbers (e.g., NA035214 TWO SHOT) - Extract line numbers (e.g., Line No: 1.000) - Extract weight, unit price, and extended amount individually 6. Header Info: - Supplier name: Must be exactly 'Stanley Engineered Fastening LLC' - Invoice number, invoice date, and page info: capture precisely - 'Sales Order No.' is the PO number (e.g., 13665335) - Data Separation: Keep tool numbers, line numbers, and customer references as distinct fields.

prompt: INVOICE EXTRACTION INSTRUCTIONS:  1. Extract company identifiers (IČO/DIČ) for both Jungheinrich and Cooper-Standard, ensuring both Czech registration numbers and VAT IDs are captured correctly.  2. Capture all three critical dates: invoice date (Dat. dokl.), due date (Datum splatnosti), and tax point date (DUZP), converting from DD.MM.YYYY to YYYY-MM-DD format.  3. For equipment rental items, extract the full rental period (Doba pronáj.), serial numbers (Výrobní číslo), and daily rate (Cena za den) into separate structured fields.  4. Ensure each line item has its position number (Poz.), article number (Artikl-číslo), description (Označení), quantity (Počet), unit of measure (JM), unit price (Cena/kus), and total price (Cena).  5. Correctly identify items with zero pricing as legitimate line items - Jungheinrich often includes batteries and chargers as separate line items with no individual pricing.  6. Extract the VAT percentage (%) and VAT amount (DPH) separately from the net amount (Cena Netto) and total amount (CELK. CENA).  7. Capture delivery information including delivery terms (Dodací podmínky), delivery address (Místo dodání), and delivery note references.  8. Extract customer order references including order number (Zákaznické č. obj.) and internal order number (Interní číslo zakázky).  9. Capture banking details including bank names, account numbers, IBANs, and BIC/SWIFT codes from the footer of the invoice.  10. prompt: INVOICE EXTRACTION INSTRUCTIONS:  1. Extract company identifiers (IČO/DIČ) for both Jungheinrich and Cooper-Standard, ensuring both Czech registration numbers and VAT IDs are captured correctly.  2. Capture all three critical dates: invoice date (Dat. dokl.), due date (Datum splatnosti), and tax point date (DUZP), converting from DD.MM.YYYY to YYYY-MM-DD format.  3. For equipment rental items, extract the full rental period (Doba pronáj.), serial numbers (Výrobní číslo), and daily rate (Cena za den) into separate structured fields.  4. Ensure each line item has its position number (Poz.), article number (Artikl-číslo), description (Označení), quantity (Počet), unit of measure (JM), unit price (Cena/kus), and total price (Cena).  5. Correctly identify items with zero pricing as legitimate line items - Jungheinrich often includes batteries and chargers as separate line items with no individual pricing.  6. Extract the VAT percentage (%) and VAT amount (DPH) separately from the net amount (Cena Netto) and total amount (CELK. CENA).  7. Capture delivery information including delivery terms (Dodací podmínky), delivery address (Místo dodání), and delivery note references.  8. Extract customer order references including order number (Zákaznické č. obj.) and internal order number (Interní číslo zakázky).  9. Capture banking details including bank names, account numbers, IBANs, and BIC/SWIFT codes from the footer of the invoice.  10. special_instructions: 1. Extract all currency amounts in Czech Koruna (CZK) using the European number format: - Thousands are separated by a dot (.) - Decimals are separated by a comma (,) - Always return the final numeric value in a standardized format with two decimal places, using the European format: 201.706,07 - Do not confuse 14.130,80 with 14.13; ensure you treat the comma as a decimal separator and dot as the thousands separator. 2. Return the complete invoice data in a well formatted JSON string only.

Column headers (like \\\"PART IDENTIFICATION\\\", \\\"Line No\\\", \\\"QTY SHIP\\\", \\\"EXT AMT\\\") are not line item descriptions - don't confuse them with actual product descriptions. 3. Line items without explicit unit prices should have zero values for price fields, not the invoice total. 4. Line items showing only reference information without explicit pricing should have zero price values. 6. Do not use \\\"Part Identification\\\" as a description - this is a column header, not the actual description. 7. For each line item, verify that the price comes from the appropriate unit price or amount column for that specific item only. 8. Differentiate between actual line items and summary information - summary totals belong in the header, not as line items. 9. Extract the Quantity and Line No for each line item:  - If a line item spans multiple pages, the quantity may appear on an earlier page, and the line number on a later one — these must be correlated and combined.  - Some items may not have a line number — in such cases, leave the line number field blank or null.  - The line number is often found in the 4th line of the item description block — parse accordingly to extract it. 10. Pay special attention to items at page breaks - these may appear to be continued items but are often distinct line items with their own quantities and values. 11. Each distinct part number and quantity combination represents a separate line item. Do not merge similar items. special_instructions: 1. Quantities: Always whole numbers followed by EA (e.g., 875.000 EA); extract as integers from the 'QTY SHIP' column. 2. Weight: The 'WT' column indicates weight, not quantity — do not confuse the two. 3. Unit Price: Includes an 'M' suffix, meaning price per thousand units — adjust calculations accordingly. 4. Extended Amount: Extract from the 'EXT AMT' column; sum all line items to validate the subtotal/total. 5. Line Items: - Extract item code from PART IDENTIFICATION (e.g., NA002472) - Capture full description as shown - Extract tool numbers (e.g., NA035214 TWO SHOT) - Extract line numbers (e.g., Line No: 1.000) - Extract weight, unit price, and extended amount individually 6. Header Info: - Supplier name: Must be exactly 'Stanley Engineered Fastening LLC' - Invoice number, invoice date, and page info: capture precisely - 'Sales Order No.' is the PO number (e.g., 13665335) - Data Separation: Keep tool numbers, line numbers, and customer references as distinct fields.

prompt: INVOICE EXTRACTION INSTRUCTIONS:    1. The overall invoice total should NEVER be assigned as a price to any individual line item. 2. Column headers (like \\\"PART IDENTIFICATION\\\", \\\"Line No\\\", \\\"QTY SHIP\\\", \\\"EXT AMT\\\") are not line item descriptions - don't confuse them with actual product descriptions. 3. Line items without explicit unit prices should have zero values for price fields, not the invoice total. 4. On the final page of multi-page invoices, distinguish between:\n   - The invoice TOTAL (belongs in header.total)\n   - Individual line items (need their own specific prices, if shown only) 5. Line items showing only reference information without explicit pricing should have zero price values. 6. Do not use \\\"Part Identification\\\" as a description - this is a column header, not the actual description. 7. For each line item, verify that the price comes from the appropriate unit price or amount column for that specific item only. 8. Differentiate between actual line items and summary information - summary totals belong in the header, not as line items. 9. Extract the Quantity and Line No for each line item:  - If a line item spans multiple pages, the quantity may appear on an earlier page, and the line number on a later one — these must be correlated and combined.  - Some items may not have a line number — in such cases, leave the line number field blank or null.  - The line number is often found in the 4th line of the item description block — parse accordingly to extract it. 10. Pay special attention to items at page breaks - these may appear to be continued items but are often distinct line items with their own quantities and values. 11. Each distinct part number and quantity combination represents a separate line item. Do not merge similar items. special_instructions: 1. Quantities: Always whole numbers followed by EA (e.g., 875.000 EA); extract as integers from the 'QTY SHIP' column. 2. Weight: The 'WT' column indicates weight, not quantity — do not confuse the two. 3. Unit Price: Includes an 'M' suffix, meaning price per thousand units — adjust calculations accordingly. 4. Extended Amount: Extract from the 'EXT AMT' column; sum all line items to validate the subtotal/total. 5. Line Items: - Extract item code from PART IDENTIFICATION (e.g., NA002472) - Capture full description as shown - Extract tool numbers (e.g., NA035214 TWO SHOT) - Extract line numbers (e.g., Line No: 1.000) - Extract weight, unit price, and extended amount individually 6. Header Info: - Supplier name: Must be exactly 'Stanley Engineered Fastening LLC' - Invoice number, invoice date, and page info: capture precisely - 'Sales Order No.' is the PO number (e.g., 13665335) - Data Separation: Keep tool numbers, line numbers, and customer references as distinct fields.

special_instructions: 1. Extract all currency amounts in Czech Koruna (CZK) using the European number format: - Thousands are separated by a dot (.) - Decimals are separated by a comma (,) - Always return the final numeric value in a standardized format with two decimal places, using the European format: 201.706,07 - Do not confuse 14.130,80 with 14.13; ensure you treat the comma as a decimal separator and dot as the thousands separator. 2. Return the complete invoice data in a well formatted JSON string only.

prompt: INVOICE EXTRACTION INSTRUCTIONS:  1. Extract company identifiers (IČO/DIČ) for both Jungheinrich and Cooper-Standard, ensuring both Czech registration numbers and VAT IDs are captured correctly.  2. Capture all three critical dates: invoice date (Dat. dokl.), due date (Datum splatnosti), and tax point date (DUZP), converting from DD.MM.YYYY to YYYY-MM-DD format.  3. For equipment rental items, extract the full rental period (Doba pronáj.), serial numbers (Výrobní číslo), and daily rate (Cena za den) into separate structured fields.  4. Ensure each line item has its position number (Poz.), article number (Artikl-číslo), description (Označení), quantity (Počet), unit of measure (JM), unit price (Cena/kus), and total price (Cena).  5. Correctly identify items with zero pricing as legitimate line items - Jungheinrich often includes batteries and chargers as separate line items with no individual pricing.  6. Extract the VAT percentage (%) and VAT amount (DPH) separately from the net amount (Cena Netto) and total amount (CELK. CENA).  7. Capture delivery information including delivery terms (Dodací podmínky), delivery address (Místo dodání), and delivery note references.  8. Extract customer order references including order number (Zákaznické č. obj.) and internal order number (Interní číslo zakázky).  9. Capture banking details including bank names, account numbers, IBANs, and BIC/SWIFT codes from the footer of the invoice.  10. special_instructions: 1. Extract all currency amounts in Czech Koruna (CZK) using the European number format: - Thousands are separated by a dot (.) - Decimals are separated by a comma (,) - Always return the final numeric value in a standardized format with two decimal places, using the European format: 201.706,07 - Do not confuse 14.130,80 with 14.13; ensure you treat the comma as a decimal separator and dot as the thousands separator. 2. Return the complete invoice data in a well formatted JSON string only. 3. Extract the tax id from the footer of the invoice. It starts with a "DIC".
